panels.title: Active Alerts

panels.description:
These metrics are pulled from the past 24 hours of records created.

INXPO is our virtual event management vendor.

c.ix_created will not match the count returned by DATA_HOURLY_ELOQUA_FORMS_created{exported_job="integration_form_inxpo"} because form submissions include both new records and modifications to current records.

Every time there is a non-unique pair of show key and offer, the alert remains active for 24 hours after the data was received (meaning if an event was watched on monday and on-demand submissions continued to be received until Friday, we would receive alerts all week despite how there may have been only one non-unique pair).

panels.description:
These should follow each other closely. 
Processing time of records from Contacts.Uploads.Members to reach Contacts.Inquiries is about 6 hours. If the timespan is larger than that, then processing is slow. 
If Contacts.Inquiries never reaches the same count as Contacts.Uploads.Members, then processing is losing records.
